*sigh* back to the drawing board. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucolcannon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Colcannon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0> at: 10/31/01 7:34:45 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ualysiaskye.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alysia Skye</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/2/01 11:26:59 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/alysiaskye/profile/alysia02.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: playstation rpgs </span><hr size=1> The combat in Xenogears isn't a Street Fighteresque  button combo sort of thing.  It's not a &quot;twitch&quot; game by any means.  Except for one mini-game arena, XG combat is completely turn based and uses an active time gauge similar to that used in the FF series.  The &quot;combos&quot; (or deathblows) with both characters and the Gears are comparable to the limit breaks in FFVII - there are just oodles more of them, you have to build up to them, and they can be strung together in a kata-style form.  Spells are handled as Ether attacks - you have ether points instead of mana points.  Most characters's ether abilities are focused on a buffing/debuffing role with only one or two offensive ether attacks.  Elly and Emerelda both have great elemental ether attacks.<br>
<br>
I've played Xenogears twice and have 30 hours into a third game.  The CG and anime sequences are beautiful and the soundtrack is awesome.  The character development, plot and story depth, and backhistory make this game the best Playstation RPG ever.  Maybe the best computer RPG, too.<br>
<br>
It's worth trying out. :)<br>
